features: 【100W USB C Fast Charging】Our uni USB C cable 10 ft supports PD 3.0 and QC 3.0 fast charging with a max 100W (20V 5A) output. And backward compatible with 100W/65W/60W/45W/20W USB C power delivery adapters. Charge your MacBook Pro up to 55% in only 35 minutes - say goodbye to low battery anxiety! Note: The actual charging speed depends on your device and wall charger.

【Play while Charging】Our 10ft/3M USB-C cable is much longer than Apple's original 6.6ft cable, making you can play while lying down and charging and no matter where the plug is. It is ideal for school, home, work, and travel when you need to reach charging outlets. Note: Does not support video output.

【Safe and Stable E-mark Chip】Our USB C to USB C cable has a built-in E-marker chip that intelligently matches the necessary current, which can effectively extend the life of the battery and the device.

【Extreme Durability】This usb c charging cable with reinforced joints provides long-lasting, tangle-free performance. Upgraded 3D aluminum connector and exclusive laser welding technology, which can ensure the metal part won't break. Perfect for daily use and heavy-duty charging.

【Universal Compatibility】 This type C cable is compatible with virtually all USB-C devices including phones, tablets, and laptops. Compatible with iPhone 15/15Pro/15Plus/15ProMax, MacBook Pro/Air, iPad Pro/Mini/Air, Dell XPS/Inspiron/Latitude ThinkPad, Samsung Galaxy Tab S8/S8 Plus, Samsung Galaxy S23/S22/S21, and etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best 100W long USB C charging cables in the market
reviews.reviewText: It's difficult to find 10 ft or longer cables for 100W USB C charging cables. Especially a more trustworthy product.Personally, I don't understand why cables in general cost much (aren't they just wires?), but I was originally burnt by a fake USB C charging cable elsewhere. In the electronics section, the 'gold standard' is generally Anker. And then there's the "other companies in China" which are often much cheaper. Well, I originally took the latter deal and how horrible of a mistake it was. The cable didn't work and I had to get a refund. Judging by the standards of most cheap 100W USB C charging cables from Chinese companies, they are all either poorly built (won't last long) or a fake product (eg: not 100W despite the claim on the cable).Well, this is my first time testing out Uni Accessories for electronics. I must say, I was astounded by the quality of the product.The cables as you can see are thick and well made. And best of all, IT WORKS. It's a 10 ft cable that WORKS. I'm sick and tired of cheaper cables which actually don't provide the wattage they claim and/or be poorly constructed.I have updated the "rankings" of which companies I should trust going forward for electronics.1. Uni Accessories2. INIU3. Anker... (a bit of drop in quality but still gets the job done)4. UGREENAnd that's it. I have heard of 'Baseus' but never had experience with a product from the company so can't believe.These are for me the 4 brands I can now 'trust' as a 'go to'.Enough with that. Back to the cable.Very well built (much better built than even an Anker equivalent). Cables are on the thicker side so it feels good quality.And it lets me charge my laptop from my bed. What more can I ask for?Personally, I wish packaging wouldn't be so big for such a product but that's a complaint which is irrelevant to the actual product itself.10 out of 10. I will add Uni Accessories into the list of companies I can trust going forward for electronics.

reviews.reviewText: The 10' USB-C to USB-C cable has reliably charged my MacBook Pros and iPad Pro 12.9" for years. This is usual for most cables on the market and even at times the metal reinforced kind.Here is well this cable differs from the rest, even OEM Apple's cables. I got out my Amazon order details, registerd on Uni's site my product and submitted a warranty claim with order details and pictures of the product. Within hours, I got a response and within days, a replacement cable was on its way.Considering the great product build, and lifetime warranty, I would highly recommend buying from UNI.
